# Task Sizing and Execution

## Good Tasks (bounded, single-layer)

- Implement ChatGPT adapter normalization
- Add canonical `Session` schema and tests
- Create evidence link repository methods
- Build local import batch viewer component
- Implement project merge scoring function

## Bad Tasks (too broad, cross-cutting)

- Build the whole app
- Make the intelligence better
- Refactor everything
- Support all imports everywhere

## Execution Rules

- Every feature starts with a brief spec in `/docs` before implementation.
- Write tests for adapters, normalization, scoring, merge logic, and pipeline stages.
- If a task crosses more than two packages, split it.
- Use Zod schemas at every boundary between packages.
- Preserve provenance — never create derived intelligence without evidence links.
- Update docs and ADRs when making architectural changes.
- Keep merge/scoring logic deterministic where possible. Use models for semantic interpretation, not for basic system correctness.

## Definition of Done

A task is not done unless: types are correct, schemas validate, tests pass, docs updated if needed, provenance preserved, privacy contract preserved, and no hidden remote behavior was introduced.

For **feature-sized or roadmap-aligned** work, also update **`docs/build-log/`** (new or updated log file + index in `docs/build-log/README.md`). See the **build-log** Cursor rule.
